Docker

to install docker

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install docker.io

thats it check if it is correctly installed or not--> by-->sudo docker run hello-world

and if it is giving masking error run following three commands
systemctl unmask docker.service
systemctl unmask docker.socket
systemctl start docker.service

and then--> sudo service docker start--> to start and sudo service docker stop-->to stop

difference between virtualization and contentarization-- virtualization madhe every vm la specific minimum resource dyave lagtat..but here flexible

 

docker resolve issue of application working on one platform and not on other 
at software development life cycle docker comes at deployment level